{
  "rationale": "This supervisor structure ensures safe navigation by enforcing recovery after obstacle detection, uses commit states to avoid oscillations, and always responds to uncontrollable events. Only one primary controllable action is enabled per state (except obs_front, which allows both move_backward and full_rotate for escape). Commit states ensure persistent action until a safe state is reached, and helper states prevent immediate re-entry into forward motion after obstacle detection.",
