  "strategy": [
    "Always respond to uncontrollable events to ensure supervisor is nonblocking.",
    "After obstacle_front, require a recovery action (move_backward or full_rotate) before resuming forward motion.",
    "Use commit states for rotation and forward movement to avoid oscillations and ensure persistent action.",
    "Allow only one primary controllable action per state (except obs_front for escape).",
    "Rotate away from side obstacles, using commit states to persist until path is clear.",
    "After recovery (escape), only return to forward motion when path is clear.",
    "Never allow immediate move_forward after obstacle_front; always pass through a recovery state.",
